        <abstract>
            <p>Reception of Scott’s paper.</p>
            <p>Difficulty of writing Boott’s obituary.</p>
            <p>Critical of Edward Frankland’s glacial theory.</p>
            <p>Falconer’s and Ramsay’s views on Himalayan lakes lack support of basic evidence.</p>
            <p>Taxonomic distribution of climbing plants.</p>
            <p>Huxley picks quarrels with minor figures and thus magnifies them.</p>
        </abstract>
